  "notes": [
    "This study compared AURKA expression and activity between HBV-associated HCC and cryptogenic HCC, finding distinct patterns of substrate phosphorylation that may have therapeutic implications.",
    "RNA quality issues prevented gene expression analysis, requiring reliance on immunohistochemical methods for protein-level assessment.",
    "The study suggests that AURKA-targeted therapies may need to be stratified by HCC etiology due to different downstream signaling patterns."
  ]
